-- Ford chairman says automaker to keep going on its own
-- 
-- Sun Jan 11, 2009 12:51pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/01/11/us-ford-sb-idUSTRE50A23D20090111

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Ford Motor Co ( F.N ) Chairman Bill Ford said on Sunday that the company's "game plan is to keep going on our own," and not to tap a U.S. line of credit. 

 Highlights: * Bill Ford says government stimulus needed for consumers to buy hybrids if gas prices stay low * Bill Ford says expects gas prices to rise as U.S. economy recovers * Bill Ford says any government incentives to help U.S. consumers buy cars would be great * Bill Ford says any "entire economy certainly needs help" * Bill Ford says "right now we're comfortable" but have asked for line of credit in case "the world implodes as we know it" * CEO mulally says U.S. clearly in recession, confident monetary and fiscal policy around the world will get economy going